[In the past 24 hours, 15 countries including the USA (102 375), Iran (40 808), India (27 429), UK (25 090), Turkey (23 731), Indonesia (20 709), Russia (22 160), Mexico (20 018), Thailand (19 603), Malaysia (17 236), Japan (14 733), Brazil (12 471), Spain (13 212), Bangladesh (11 463), and Argentina (10 180) have reported the highest numbers of cases, all reporting more than 10 000 newly confirmed cases. A global total of 8639 deaths were reported in the past 24 hours (late 7 Aug 2021 to late 8 Aug 2021). A total of 48 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours; 20 of the 48 countries are from the European region, 7 are from the Americas region, 6 are from the Eastern Mediterranean region, 5 are from the South East Asia region, 6 are from the Western Pacific region, and 4 from the African region.

Comparing the 7-day averages of daily confirmed cases from the past 7 days and those from 8-14 days ago, case counts have increased by 7.4%, while daily reported deaths have increased by 2.1%. Similar comparative 7-day averages in the USA show a 45.3% increase in daily reported cases and a 39.4% increase in reported deaths.

Impression: The global daily reported over 650 000 newly confirmed infections in the past 24 hours with over 204.13 million cumulative reported cases and over 4.31 million reported deaths. - Mod.UBA]
